    "narrative_summary": "The BRCA2 c.1141G>A (p.Asp381Asn) missense change is a germline variant observed in the context of hereditary breast and ovarian cancer susceptibility. A large\u2011scale multifactorial likelihood analysis classified this variant as likely benign, providing strong statistical support for a benign interpretation while noting that ClinVar contains conflicting entries ranging from likely benign to uncertain significance [PMC6772163]. The same nucleotide change is mentioned in the supplementary material of several unrelated studies\u2014one describing a C. elegans heat\u2011shock protein variant, another reporting ethnic\u2011specific BRCA variant spectra in a Chinese cohort, and a third listing it among clinical data for mycosis fungoides\u2014none of which offer additional functional or clinical interpretation for the BRCA2 alteration [PMC8166903][PMC6617753][PMC6282857]. Taken together, the preponderance of evidence points toward a benign or likely benign classification for BRCA2 c.1141G>A, although the presence of discordant ClinVar submissions introduces a modest degree of uncertainty that could be resolved with further functional or segregation data.",
    "structured_summary": {
        "overall_pathogenicity": "benign",
        "pathogenicity_counts": {
            "supports pathogenicity": 0,
            "uncertain": 0,
            "supports benignity": 1
        },
        "conflicting_evidence": false
    },
